```r
```r
initial_columns_for_model <- c(\applicant_race_and_ethnicity\, 
                                 \applicant_income_000s\, 
                                 \co_applicant_race_and_ethnicity\, 
                                 \co_applicant_sex\, 
                                 \county_code\, 
                                 \hoepa_status\, 
                                 \lien_status\, 
                                 \msamd\, 
                                 \owner_occupancy\, 
                                 \preapproval\, 
                                 \property_type\, 
                                 \purchaser_type\, 
                                 \loan_amount_000s\, 
                                 \county_name\, 
                                 \applicant_sex\, 
                                 \hud_median_family_income\, 
                                 \tract_to_msamd_income\, 
                                 \loan_to_income_ratio\, 
                                 \agency_code\, 
                                 \minority_population\,
                                 \respondent_id\,
                                 \loan_purpose\,
                                 \loan_purpose_name\,
                                 \rate_spread\,
                                 \population\,
                                 \number_of_owner_occupied_units\)
  
df_for_model <- hmda_data_df[initial_columns_for_model]
df_for_model$log_loan_amount_000s <- log(df_for_model$loan_amount_000s)
df_for_model$log_applicant_income_000s <- log(df_for_model$applicant_income_000s)
df_for_model$loan_granted <- ifelse(hmda_data_df$action_taken == 1 | hmda_data_df$action_taken == 6, \yes\, \no\)

df_for_model$co_applicant_present <- NA
  df_for_model$co_applicant_present <- ifelse( df_for_model$co_applicant_race_and_ethnicity == \White\ | df_for_model$co_applicant_race_and_ethnicity == \Black or African American\ | df_for_model$co_applicant_race_and_ethnicity == \Hispanic or Latino\ | df_for_model$co_applicant_race_and_ethnicity == \Asian\ | df_for_model$co_applicant_race_and_ethnicity == \Native Hawaiian or Other Pacific Islander\ | df_for_model$co_applicant_race_and_ethnicity == \American Indian or Alaska Native\, 1, 0)
  df_for_model$applicant_race_and_ethnicity <- as.factor(df_for_model$applicant_race_and_ethnicity)
  df_for_model$co_applicant_sex <- as.factor(df_for_model$co_applicant_sex)
  df_for_model$co_applicant_present <- as.factor(df_for_model$co_applicant_present)
  df_for_model$county_code <- df_for_model$county_code
  df_for_model$hoepa_status <- as.factor(df_for_model$hoepa_status)
  df_for_model$lien_status <- as.factor(df_for_model$lien_status)
  df_for_model$preapproval <- as.factor(df_for_model$preapproval)
  df_for_model$property_type <- as.factor(df_for_model$property_type)
  df_for_model$purchaser_type <- as.factor(df_for_model$purchaser_type)
  df_for_model$applicant_sex <- as.factor(df_for_model$applicant_sex)
  df_for_model$county_code <- as.integer(df_for_model$county_code)
  df_for_model$county_name <- as.factor(df_for_model$county_name)
  df_for_model$agency_code <- as.factor(df_for_model$agency_code)
  df_for_model$owner_occupancy <- as.factor(df_for_model$owner_occupancy)
  df_for_model$loan_granted <- as.factor(df_for_model$loan_granted)
  # We have 1024 respondent ids in PA for e.g Remove dashes from the
  # id and convert it to an integer column
  df_for_model$respondent_id <- gsub(\-\, \\, df_for_model$respondent_id)
  df_for_model$respondent_id <- as.numeric(df_for_model$respondent_id)
  df_for_model$loan_purpose <- as.factor(df_for_model$loan_purpose)
  df_for_model$loan_purpose_name <- as.factor(df_for_model$loan_purpose_name)

set.seed(400)

split_dfs <- train_test_split(df_for_model$loan_granted, df_for_model)

train <- split_dfs[[1]]
test <- split_dfs[[2]]

<!-- rnb-text-begin -->

## CART Algorithm
Classification and Regression Trees (CART) split attributes based on values that minimize a loss function, such as sum of squared errors.

From the selected columns in EDA for feature importances, we select top features and build a model using those predictors. 

<!-- rnb-text-end -->


<!-- rnb-chunk-begin -->


<!-- rnb-source-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYGBgclxuYGBgclxubGlicmFyeShycGFydClcbiNDcmVhdGUgTW9kZWxcbmNhcnRfbW9kZWxfYmFzaWMgPC0gcnBhcnQobG9hbl9ncmFudGVkfmxpZW5fc3RhdHVzK3B1cmNoYXNlcl90eXBlK2FnZW5jeV9jb2RlK2FwcGxpY2FudF9yYWNlX2FuZF9ldGhuaWNpdHkrYXBwbGljYW50X2luY29tZV8wMDBzK2NvdW50eV9jb2RlLHRyYWluLGNvbnRyb2wgPSBycGFydC5jb250cm9sKGNwID0gMCkpXG5cbnByZWQubW9kZWwuMSA8LSBwcmVkaWN0KGNhcnRfbW9kZWxfYmFzaWMsdGVzdCx0eXBlID0gXFxjbGFzc1xcKVxuY29uZnVzaW9uTWF0cml4KHByZWQubW9kZWwuMSx0ZXN0JGxvYW5fZ3JhbnRlZClcbmBgYFxuYGBgIn0= -->

```r
```r
library(rpart)
#Create Model
cart_model_basic <- rpart(loan_granted~lien_status+purchaser_type+agency_code+applicant_race_and_ethnicity+applicant_income_000s+county_code,train,control = rpart.control(cp = 0))

pred.model.1 <- predict(cart_model_basic,test,type = \class\)
confusionMatrix(pred.model.1,test$loan_granted)

## Now we try a different tree algorithm. The C4.5 algorithm is an extension of the ID3 algorithm and constructs a decision tree to maximize information gain (difference in entropy).

library(RWeka)

c4.5_model <- J48(loan_granted~lien_status+purchaser_type+agency_code+loan_to_income_ratio+applicant_race_and_ethnicity+applicant_income_000s+county_code,train)

pred <- predict(c4.5_model,test,type = \class\)
confusionMatrix(pred,test$loan_granted)
